# Plan: Fix Prisma "undefined@P1" Error (SQL Server)

The login failure is caused by a `PrismaClientKnownRequestError` indicating that a column named `undefined` does not exist. This is a common issue when using Prisma 7 with the SQL Server driver adapter (`@prisma/adapter-mssql`) without the required `driverAdapters` preview feature enabled, or when the generated client is out of sync.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Prisma Configuration

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/prisma/schema.prisma)
- Add `previewFeatures = ["driverAdapters"]` to the `generator client` block. This is required for the custom SQL Server adapter to function correctly.

### [Component] Server Maintenance

#### [RUN] Client Generation
- Run `npx prisma generate` in the `server` directory to rebuild the client with the new feature flag.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run the recently created debug script: `npx tsx scratch/debug_prisma.ts`
- Expect `prisma.user.count()` and `prisma.user.findFirst()` to succeed.

### Manual Verification
- Attempt to login via the application UI (which uses `tkymeu@gmail.com`).
- Check server logs for successful login info.
